Scoped styles only prepend \`[data-vm-scope=\"...\"] \` to selectors. Vue 3's scoped CSS pseudo-classes are missing:

- \`:deep(.child)\` — target child component elements
- \`:global(.class)\` — escape scoping for global rules
- \`:slotted(.class)\` — target slotted content

These are essential for real-world scoped styling.